			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>PIL: A Platform Independent Language for Retargetable DSLs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ZefHemel.html">Zef Hemel</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_17">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_17</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2d.html"><span class="tagM">T2D: Deployment</span></a><ul><li> The emphasis is on platform independence and retargeting DSL implementations across back-ends.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Retargeting typically involves compilation/code generation from the DSL to multiple targets.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> PIL is introduced as a language to support building/retargeting DSLs.
</li></ul></li></ul>
